-- Dollar Advances After WSJ Reports Geithner Said Currencies `In Alignment'
-- B y   N a o t o   H o s o d a
-- 2010-10-21T01:41:31Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-10-21/dollar-advances-after-wsj-reports-geithner-said-currencies-in-alignment-.html
The dollar gained on a Wall Street
Journal quoted U.S. Treasury Secretary Timothy F. Geithner as 
saying the major currencies are “roughly in alignment now.” 
The dollar climbed to 81.60 yen as of 10:39 a.m. in Tokyo from 
81.09 yesterday in New York. Geithner spoke in an interview.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Naoto Hosoda at 
 nhosoda@bloomberg.net  